    <description>Ancient, slow-moving, gentle and tough, stoneslimes are native to many of the rimworlds. Similar to many slimes, stoneslimes produce material through strange digestive processes; in the case of stoneslimes, they produce chunks of rock. Due to their lithic nature, they are comfortable with extreme cold and heat, and are resistant to most forms of damage. Most stoneslimes are very large and hit extremely hard when they do catch an enemy, with most cases ending in the crushing of the unfortunate victim. They have no need for biting, and tend to simply roll over their foes. This variety produces chunks of sandstone.</description>
